author: dblevins
msg: Still a work in progress, but too much time and energy in it to risk loosing.  This proof-of-concept code creates a peer-to-peer network using NIO and a single thread to read/write to all peers in the network, with no duplicate connections and the ability to discover new peers from other peers.
The ultimate goal is to develop a TCP replacement for our multicast (UDP) discovery.

author: bryanduxbury
msg: THRIFT-754. java: Improvements to varint reading in Compact Protocol
This patch makes readVarint32 about 30% faster and readVarint64 about 25% faster (when using transports that support direct buffer access).
